Package: processALA
Type: Package
Title: Fetch and Filter ALA Occurrence Data for Plants
Version: 0.5.4
Authors@R: person("Peter D.", "Wilson", email = "peter.d.wilson@rbgsyd.nsw.gov.au", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Peter D. Wilson <peterdonaldwilson@gmail.com>
Description: A set of functions to fetch, filter and clean plant occurrence records from the Atlas of Living Australia (ALA). Filtered and cleaned data are written to csv-formatted text files for subsequent use. Three output files may be produced: herbarium records, human observations, and records from systematic vegetation surveys which are part of the NSW Vegetation Information System (VIS).
Depends: R (>= 4.1)
Imports: sp,
  sf,
  dplyr,
  galah,
  httr
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: false
RoxygenNote: 7.2.2
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
